##40,000 packets of Sanitary Napkins on the hot search, in this to the front-line female medical staff donated hygiene supplies relay, Shanghai the first action

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

In the National People up and down the fight against the epidemic, while Shanghai has not forgotten the body in the front line of "they" .

Reporter | Ying Chen

How long does it take to wear a protective suit on the front line? In the vast majority of reports at the moment, it's eight hours, but in reality it can sometimes be even longer. For fear of wasting supplies, doctors and nurses often wear diapers and insist on not going to the bathroom until the job is done.

Also in the vast majority of reports, due to the shortage of first-line protective materials, the relevant organizations, enterprises, individuals to the epidemic first-line donated masks, protective clothing, goggles and other protective supplies story is also common in the news.

But there is one demand that, although it has been flowing, is not so loud that it was initially given as much attention as protective material. This demand is the first-line medical staff for physiological needs.

To what extent is there a shortage of Feminine hygiene on the Front Lines? From the related topics on Weibo, one can see a forelock

First-line nurses endure physical pain, to the head nurse application for two days have not been able to get sanitary supplies.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Hainan nurses who supported the shelter hospital had to rely on diapers and "blood mixed with urine" .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A Hebei Medical Team of Nurses Menstrual period, pants are soaked. But she cried and didn't want to come out to change, just to save a suit.

Sadly, in the absence of hygiene supplies, physiological needs are not taken care of, some front-line staff even choose to take short-acting birth control pills to delay menstruation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On Feb. 7, Weibo User@liang Yustacey launched a campaign on the topic of sister relief against the epidemic, calling for donations of menstrual care supplies to female health care workers in the front line.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A few days ago, the Hashtag # 40,000 packets of sanitary napkins arrived in Wuhan. Nearly 40,000 packets of Sanitary Napkins, urgently raised by the China Women's Development Foundation, have arrived in Wuhan and are being distributed to female medical staff on the front line of the epidemic, the report said. The Hubei Provincial Women's Federation arranged for the pads to be distributed to health care workers in Wuhan, Wuchang District and Qingshan District, Wuhan, as well as to health care workers at the Tongji Hospital affiliated to the Tongji Medical College.

In fact, Shanghai was the first in the relay to donate medical supplies to frontline female medical staff. The Shanghai Women's Federation was the first in the country to raise money for first-line female doctors and nurses for menstrual supplies.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 1, the MWF, the M38 Red Flag Bearer Association and the Antai Emba Linxiu Group of Jiaotong University collected women-only Koala Pants and sent them to 33 hospitals in Wuhan and related hospitals in Huanggang.

As early as January 31, the Shanghai Women's Federation and the women workers'committee of the Municipal Federation of Trade Unions launched an initiative, hope that there are Koala Pants (for women's menstrual care and other products, such as positive corporate donations, or below the market price of love to provide supplies; at the same time accept cash donations, fund-raising funds dedicated to the purchase of Koala Pants and other products.

A slip of the tongue triggered a 48-hour emergency

"there must be a shortage of protective equipment... you know, suits they wear for eight hours at a time. At normal times, it was fine, but when the female doctors and nurses had their periods, it was really hard..."January 31, shanghai Women's Federation in Ruijin Hospital doctors to understand the needs of the front line, this casual words, caused the city's Women's Federation highly valued.

On that day, the Shanghai Women's Federation learned from the medical and Health Organization that supports the front line of the epidemic that more than 50 percent of the doctors are women and more than 90 percent of the first-line nurses are women. In the female menstrual period, Sanitary Napkins should be replaced up to 2 hours, otherwise easy to breed bacteria.

How to keep them engaged in high intensity work, and considering the special situation of first line anti epidemic work, Weng Wenlei, vice chairman and spokesman of the Shanghai Women's Federation, told Xinmin Weekly, some special health care items, such as Koalas and pull-up pants, seem more practical, allowing female front-line staff to minimize the number of times they take off their protective clothing.

Here's an idea. How do you get an idea to land. Coincidentally, the Shanghai Children's Fund, which is run by the municipal women's Federation, has just been approved by the Civil Affairs Department to expand its donor base. "UNICEF usually targets children under the age of 18. But in the past, whenever we had a major disaster, UNICEF would apply to the civil affairs department in Advance to expand the scope of donations, " Weng told reporters, upon hearing the good news, the Municipal Women's Federation immediately donated Koala Pants to the first-line female medical staff.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
February 1 evening at 5:00, the municipal women's Federation, the Municipal Children's Fund, the Municipal Women Entrepreneurs Association first 100 boxes (9,600 pieces) of women-only Koala Pants riding is about to go to Wuhan, the pick-up truck shipment

After comprehensive consideration, all the donated items were donated not only to the female staff of the Shanghai medical team to Wuhan, but also to the frontline female medical staff of the Shanghai Municipal Clinical Center for Public Health and the Shanghai Municipal Center for Disease Control and Prevention, and 110 first-line female medical personnel of fever clinic in Shanghai.

The quantity and amount of materials raised for donation are calculated based on the number of people, the price, etc. , "If everyone is menstruating for about four days and using at least three pads a day, then everyone needs at least 12 pads a month. We wanted to get people to donate a month's worth, so we offered to donate the first 50,000. The average estimated price of a piece of Koala Pants is about $6, so $300,000 was raised."

That night, the Municipal Women's Federation's proposal on the website, wechat public accounts, the municipal women's Federation of various groups and other platforms released.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The next day, the municipal women's Federation's telephone was "beat up" ! "I didn't expect people to respond so quickly. I was very moved that many citizens donated money, 100,200,500 yuan in this way, " Weng said, the initiative also received strong support from the Association of Women Entrepreneurs, with some members immediately donating Koalas, others offering free transportation and hospitals accepting them, "We sent them to them, and they were very grateful. We didn't run into any reluctance, we didn't run into any obstacles, it was very smooth. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 6, the Municipal Women's Federation and the Municipal Children's Fund donated materials to assist Hubei families

February 1 evening at 5:00, the first batch of 100 boxes (9,600 pieces) women-only Koala Pants will be "boarded" on the truck bound for Wuhan. As of that day, the project has raised nearly 2 million yuan worth of materials and donations, far exceeding the city women's Federation First Collection Goals.

Within 48 hours of the launch, the first supplies arrived in Wuhan on the afternoon of February 2 and were immediately delivered to medical staff. At the same time, the donation of Koala Pants to the city's female medical staff has also been assembled for shipment.

At 5 p.m. on February 1, the first shipment of 100 cases of Koala Pants was shipped

As of February 12, the Shanghai Women's Federation and the Shanghai Children's Fund had sent and mobilized 58,820 pieces of Koalas and Adult diaper to local hospitals in Shanghai, Xiaogan, Huanggang and Suizhou.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 19, the municipal women's Federation, the Municipal Children's Fund and the Municipal Women Entrepreneurs Association donated 100 boxes of Safety Pants to Xiaogan City Center hospital

As of February 26, more than 130,000 pieces of Koala Pants had been donated by the Shanghai Women's Federation with strong support and broad participation, according to the latest figures.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 18,1,086 boxes of sanitary articles such as diapers donated by the municipal women's Federation, the Municipal Children's Fund and the King of Japan Company arrived in Xiaogan by post air and special transport, and were distributed to the relevant medical institutions in the prefectures, cities and municipalities directly under the city

The reporter learned that the Shanghai Women's Federation not only collected physiological and health supplies for women, on February 13, the Shanghai Municipal Women's Federation, the Shanghai Women's and children's Service and Guidance Center (women's Garden) and the Shanghai Municipal Center for the development of Women's social organizations jointly launched the "mask" protection front, giving love to the most needy people in the face mask collection campaign, call on municipal women's social organizations will "epidemic" front-line shortage of urgently needed masks to save down, donated to the people in need.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The municipal women's Federation and other organizations jointly launched the "cover" to protect the front line, send love to the most needy people mask collection action

So far, a total of 55,317 masks (including two goggles) have been donated by municipal women's social organizations, members and caring enterprises, of these, 54,147 masks (including two goggles) have been sent to the eighth batch of Shanghai Hubei Medical Aid team and hospitals in need in Shanghai area in batches. The remaining 1,170 masks will be sent to the next batch of Hubei Medical Aid team.

In Shanghai, the needs of women are always being seen

Soon, the first action by Shanghai to support the first line of health supplies for female medical personnel has been an increasing number of institutions and individuals support.

The China Women's Development Foundation, which is affiliated to the all-china Women's Federation, urgently raised 2.25 million yuan in targeted assistance for first-line female medical personnel, the People's Daily said on its official microblog on Feb. 14, among them, 200,000 yuan is used for the targeted purchase of safety pants, 2020 boxes of sanitary Napkins worth 1 million yuan, 20,000 pairs of safety pants worth 50,000 yuan and long-johns worth 1 million yuan. The first batch of 20,000 safety pants will arrive in Wuhan in the near future.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Nearly 40,000 bags of Sanitary Napkins, urgently raised by the China Women's Development Foundation, have arrived in Wuhan and have been distributed to female medical staff on the front line of the epidemic, the Xinhua news agency said on Feb. 18.

The predicament of the first-line female medical staff was gradually resolved. But it also exposed another problem in people's subjective consciousness.

Some people think that feminine hygiene products are not essential. Some people question whether an aunt scarf is as important as a mask? Even some people say that when human life is at stake, there is no time to care about "crotch thing. ".

Whether it is a lack of physical knowledge, or psychological deliberately devalue the normal physiological process of menstruation, these acts of indifference are contemptible.

During the anti-epidemic Campaign, General Secretary Xi Jinping said that the safety and health of the people should be given top priority. Similarly, Xi has repeatedly stressed the need to adhere to the basic state policy of gender equality. Don't retrograde women, their safety and health, need to be cared for?

As the People's Daily puts it in its review of women walking in reverse, respect is more important than praise

"A nurse at Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital told the media that she was overdrawn during her menstrual period, and when it was aired, the word 'menstrual period' was gone. It was confusing. "

"However, there are journalists who are keen to report that nurses who are nine months pregnant are in protective clothing on the front line, and those who have had a miscarriage for only 10 days are back on the front line... Encouraging such extreme behaviour and considering the harm to the mother and the baby and the threat to their health? Even if it is voluntary, the job of the media should be to dissuade rather than glorify."

"Back to the live broadcast of a female nurse with her head shaved in tears, there is at least a lack of empathy and compassion. "

In fact, such a report itself is not malicious, and even the hearts of journalists are indeed "moved. ". But it also shows, at least, that the sense of respect and love for women is far from universal. Perhaps, when people can openly discuss the first-line female menstrual needs, the society is normal, safe and warm.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The female health care workers who are stuck at their posts every day and at high risk of exposure are still enduring a primal pain and embarrassment as women

Fortunately, in the National People up and down the fight against the epidemic, while Shanghai has not forgotten the body in the front line of "they" .

"One team that is easy to miss is our nursing team. "We care for our sisters as much as you think our doctors are important, " Zhang Wenhong, head of the Shanghai Medical Care Expert Group and head of the infection department at Mount Hua Hospital, said in an earlier interview, are Now singing the praises of the doctors, but the more complete version would be the medical staff.

"when we approached the male leaders in charge of the docking work in each district in the course of promoting the donation, they were also very active in helping, and did not feel that it was not important at all, " Weng said, "there is now a very good foundation for implementing the basic state policy of gender equality and mainstreaming gender awareness into policy-making. We hope to see similar situations in the future, where supplies needed by women in special times will be given attention at the outset and will be included in the procurement of support materials by the relevant government departments, supplemented by social forces."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Shanghai Qingpu District community hospital receives donation from Municipal Women's Federation
